name: NYDailyNews
text:
Rhode Island mailed out 176 tax refund checks carrying Mickey Mouse’s signature on lines meant for the the general treasurer and state controller.

The misprints occurred due to a “technical error” and have been voided.
https://t.co/FLjBIUZssS

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Oklahoma man caught a world-record 150-pound paddlefish — breaking the record set last month in the same lake.

The fish was first caught in 1997 when it was 2 years old as part of a research effort by an Oklahoma State grad student.
https://t.co/H5S4kX8aml

text:
Suzyn Waldman made good on a years-long promise to Gerrit Cole to sing the National Anthem after telling him he'd one day be a great Yankee.

Waldman has sung the national anthem many times before, but this one was special.
https://t.co/3YlhOjCElP

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Microsoft is in talks to buy TikTok.

A sale to Microsoft would theoretically work for all parties: TikTok wouldn’t get banned, ByteDance could stop dealing with blustering American politicians and Microsoft would acquire Gen Z’s favorite app.
https://t.co/9TYGeD8fbw

text:
"Game of Thrones" was voted the No. 1 TV series of the 21st century by British entertainment website Digital Spy.

The runner-up spot is the supernatural Netflix program “Stranger Things,” while U.K. mainstay “Doctor Who” takes third place.
https://t.co/v4wy3PDWjH

text:
Six ex-Houston cops were indicted after a fatal drug raid.

The former officers allegedly falsified documentation about drug payments to confidential informants, routinely used false information to get search warrants and fabricated police reports.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
An ultra-Orthodox Jewish live chicken-killing ritual is akin to a wet market, animal advocates write in new legal papers.

The Kaporos ritual takes place on Brooklyn streets ahead of Yom Kippur. Some 50,000 to 100,000 live chickens are killed at gatherings
https://t.co/jcqL4NqSTI
